23.61	Cuirass	Cuirass	A cuirass is a piece of armour, formed of a single or multiple pieces of metal or other rigid material, which covers the front of the torso. In a suit of armour this important piece was generally connected to a back piece and cuirass could refer to the complete torso-protecting armour.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Cuirasse-1854-p1030165.jpg/220px-Cuirasse-1854-p1030165.jpg
